title: For Sale:  Unique Charter Arms 9 mm 5 shot revolver
postcontent: SOLD$325 with original box and paperwork.(price reduction through this coming weekend)I bought this gun from Marksman Shooting in Westfield last January.I love a revolver for a CC and I thought a 9mm would be great since I have a bunch of it and it is less expensive that the .38 special to shoot.I found that if you are running over a box of shells through at the range it becomes harder to extract the empty shells after shooting, but doable.My research shows that this is typical for this gun (other manufacturers like S/W had the same issues, but theirs cost over $1000).I sent it back to Charter Arms (lifetime warranty and great customer service) just to have it checked out and they put in a new cylinder and extractor rod in it, and shot it 50 rounds.They also recommended keeping this gun very clean, even after only 50 rounds.I now have the peace of mind that it is in working parameters.I put several cylinders through it and it shoots fine.You just have to work with it to get spent shells out if you are going to be shooting boxes of shells.If you are going to use it for a CC, it will go bang every time, but if wanting to shoot boxes of shells at a time for a range gun: not so much.If I needed it for a CC, I would not sell it, but I have 2 other J-frame revolvers in .38 special.I bought this Charter Arms just to have some fun with 9mm in a revolver to shoot some of my 9mm up at the range.This Charter has a hammer and at the time my other J-frame didn’t (Smith 642), and since then I’ve picked up another .38 special with a hammer: a Taurus 85 and I simply don't have a need for it anymore.Other prices I’ve found for this gun:$438 Buds Gun Shop Charter Arms 79920 Pitbull 5RD 9mm 2.2"$425 CHARTER ARMS PITBULL 9MM 9 MM 2" SS 5RD 79920.$499 Learn more about Featured Auctions.$428 Buyer's Club Non-Member $450.Charter Arms Pitbull, Revolver, 9mm, 2.2...Barrel is threaded into frame for added strength.Fewer internal parts for better reliability.No side plate means a more powerful frame.Strong frame locks cylinder yoke into place other revolvers use a small retention screw, which can loosen.4-point cylinder lock-up encompasses the collar, crane, cylinder stop, and hand.Full hammer block safety system: trigger must be in full firing position before hammer falls.100% American-madeBacked by Charter's lifetime warrantyA review of the gun. (for those not familiar with using the 9mm in a revolver):February 24, 2017 by KenI’ve been a law enforcement officer for the past 29 years. This revolver mechanically and cosmetically is not at the same level of a $1000 plus firearm, nor is it purported or expected to be. Charter Arms does not manufacture museum quality handguns. The do build durable, reliable weapons with superior quality components where it counts (like the beryllium copper firing pins which are widely regarded as unbreakable.)Similarly, the action which boast fewer parts than most other double action revolvers, is robust and reliable but lacks the refinement of a S&W.
